From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate type initialization closure

HIL startup telemetry shows the static-type loop alternating between the
large lifecycle caller and typeobject helpers for every builtin type.  Move
the lifecycle translation unit and the measured surviving type-ready
closure into explicit overlay group 7 so the loop stays in one Hub image.

Keep the current-thread-state, decref deallocator, and error-query leaves in
Hub.  Their measured linked net cost is 224 bytes, within the 292-byte raw
image margin before this change, and prevents group 7 from being evicted for
these startup-hot services.  The attributes are P2-only and remain empty on
all other targets.
---

